BriefDescription: Retired instructions.
Retired macro-ops.
Retired branch instructions (all types of architectural control flow changes, including exceptions and interrupts).
Retired branch instructions that were mispredicted.
Retired taken branch instructions (all types of architectural control flow changes, including exceptions and interrupts).
Retired taken branch instructions that were mispredicted.
Retired far control transfers (far call, far jump, far return, IRET, SYSCALL and SYSRET, plus exceptions and interrupts). Far control transfers are not subject to branch prediction.
Retired near returns (RET or RET Iw).
Retired near returns that were mispredicted. Each misprediction incurs the same penalty as that of a mispredicted conditional branch instruction.
Retired indirect branch instructions that were mispredicted (only EX mispredicts). Each misprediction incurs the same penalty as that of a mispredicted conditional branch instruction.
Retired indirect branch instructions.
Retired conditional branch instructions.
Cycles where the divider is busy.
Divide ops executed.
Cycles where the thread does not retire any ops due to a lack of valid ops in the retire queue (may be caused by front-end bottlenecks or pipeline redirects).
Cycles where the thread does not retire any ops as the oldest retire slot is waiting to be marked as completed.
Cycles where the thread does not retire any ops due to other reasons (retire breaks, traps, faults, etc.).
Cycles where the thread does not retire any ops as thread arbitration did not select the current thread.
Cycles where the thread does not retire any ops due to missing load completion.
Retired microcoded instructions.
Retired microcode ops.
Retired conditional branch instructions that were mispredicted due to direction mismatch.
Retired unconditional indirect near branch instructions that were mispredicted.
Retired unconditional branch instructions.
Execution IBS tagged ops.
Execution IBS tagged ops that retired.
Execution IBS periodic counter rollovers due to a previous tagged op not being IBS complete.
Execution IBS tagged ops that retired but were discarded due to IBS filtering.
Execution IBS tagged ops that resulted in a valid sample and an IBS interrupt.
Retired fused instructions.
Memory Profiler IBS tagged ops.
Memory Profiler IBS tagged ops that retired.
Memory Profiler IBS periodic counter rollovers due to a previous tagged op not being IBS complete.
Memory Profiler IBS tagged ops that retired but were discarded due to IBS filtering.
Memory Profiler IBS tagged ops that resulted in a valid sample and an IBS interrupt.
